text: The Protectorate of Bohemia and Moravia was a partially-annexed territory of Nazi Germany that was created on 16 March 1939 after the German occupation of the Czech lands. The protectorate's population was mostly ethnic Czech. The territory became the Third Czechoslovak Republic in 1945. ==References== Category:Nazi Germany Category:1939 establishments in Europe Category:1945 disestablishments in Europe Category:History of the Czech Republic
